      <biogHist id="md5-4ad97bd04a03c581e3c4e5b13bbe692f">
        <p>Agronomist, Sociologist, 1909-1979.  C.A.S. Hynam joined the University as assistant professor  of sociology in 1962 after holding various public service positions in agriculture and education in  the Caribbean.  He became a full professor in 1973.  From 1965 to 1972 he held a joint  appointment with the Department of Agricultural Economics.  He continued to teach part-time after his retirement in 1974.  A specialist in rural sociology, he conducted research and acted as a  consultant on community development and agricultural education.</p>
      </biogHist>
